          <p><span class=3D"font-semibold">Problem.</span> The design spec =
(=C2=A73) defines an <span class=3D"font-mono text-sm">events</span> module=
 ("single write path, SSE fan-out, OTel emission") that was never built; it=
s jobs landed inside <span class=3D"font-mono text-sm">InstanceStore</span>=
. A status <span class=3D"font-mono text-sm">UPDATE</span> now re-reads the=
 whole row plus the full event list to assemble a span payload (store.ts:22=
0-239), the persistence module holds live SSE listener state (store.ts:100,=
 257), and <span class=3D"font-mono text-sm">EngineHost</span>, which owns =
the run lifecycle, holds no telemetry reference at all.</p>
          <p><span class=3D"font-semibold">Solution.</span> Carve the modul=
e out: append + subscribe as its interface, with span assembly and fan-out =
as implementation. InstanceStore becomes a pure persistence adapter behind =
it; SSE and OTel become two more adapters at the same seam.</p>
